   "master_statement": "Using volume integrals, determine the volume and mass of a fluid of constant density \\(\\rho\\) in the following container filled up to the top. Determine the integrals by summing thin slices of height d\\(z\\) over the \\(z\\)-direction.",   "media": [
      "TriangularPrism.png"
   ],
   "parts": [
      {
         "statement": "",
         "responses": [
            {
               "pre_response_text": "V = ",
               "response": {
                  "mode": "Maple",
                  "mapleAnswer": "(1/2)*w*b*h"
               }
            },
			{
               "pre_response_text": "m = ",
               "response": {
                  "mode": "Maple",
                  "mapleAnswer": "(rho/2)*w*b*h"
               }
            }
         ],
		 "input_symbols":[
          [
            "\\(\\rho\\)",
            "rho"
          ]
		 ],
         "final_answer": {
            "text": "\\(V=\\frac{1}{2}wbh\\), \\(m=\\frac{\\rho}{2}wbh\\)"
         },
         "worked_solutions": [
            {
               "text": "The volume can be determined by: \\(V=\\int_{D}^{}dV\\)"
            },
            {
               "text": "Taking a horizontal slice of thickness \\(dz\\): <br>\\(dV=WB(z)dz\\)"
            },
            {
               "text": "Using congruence of triangles : <br>\\(\\frac{B(z)}{z}=\\frac{b}{h}\\)"
            },
            {
               "text": "The mass can be determined by:<br>\\(m=\\int_{D}^{}dm\\), where \\(dm\\) is element of mass defined by \\(dm=\\rho dV\\)"
            },
            {
               "text": "Since \\(\\rho\\) is constant , \\(m=\\rho\\int_{D}^{}dV=\\rho V\\)"
            },
            {
               "text": "Substitute in volume equation from earlier"
            },
            {
               "text": "\\(m=\\frac{\\rho}{2}wbh\\)"
            }
         ]
      }
